description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Apprenticeship Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Type: &lt;/strong&gt;Fixed Term 18 months&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary Range: &lt;/strong&gt;£9,903 - £17,105 per annum pro rata&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are growing our team!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you committed to providing excellent patient care in a nurturing and supportive environment? This post offers an exciting opportunity on Ward 12 to provide high standard care to Medical patients. Experience in Medicine is not essential, as training and support will be provided. You will become part of a motivated and ambitious team who will welcome and support you through your career development.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates should possess a positive and flexible approach to work and have excellent communication skills . Candidates must have some previous health care experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We operate on a 12.5 – hour shift pattern on both day and night duty.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We work closely with the practice development team to ensure that we help you develop new skills and are supported in your work. As part of this, successful candidates would take part in an induction programme, which has proven to be a valuable support to many of the health care workers joining our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an apprentice you will be trained in the full range of nursing skills. You will use these skills to meet the needs of the patient in a safe, caring environment that promotes dignity, privacy and respect, under appropriate supervision. You must be able to prioritise your own work to meet deadlines, have the ability to follow instructions and have excellent communication skills, both verbal and written. You will be confident, have a mature and flexible approach, be a good time keeper and have the ability to work unsupervised to ensure the effective coordination of duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we will ensure that you receive all the training you need to be able to do this role fully and competently. You will be released for study once a fortnight and supported to achieve a framework of nationally recognised qualifications. You will receive 27 days annual leave and be entitled to a range of discounts on services and products from a number of retailers and organisations in the local area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Entry Criteria:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2 GCSEs 3-2/D – E or level 1 Functional Skills in English and maths (or equivalent qualifications).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants are not eligible to apply for this apprenticeship if they have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Health &amp; Social Care NVQ qualification or apprenticeship (in the same field) at level 2 or level 3&lt;/strong&gt; (If applicants have other qualifications that relate to Health &amp; Social Care, an eligibility check will need to be completed to ensure they are eligible to do this apprenticeship)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note that this vacancy will close when we receive sufficient completed applications.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rachel Davies (Ward Manager) or Stacey Brown (Matron) &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tel: 01642 854512&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
